<H1>Using Electronic Mail</H1>

<P>Every UNIX system allows you to exchange electronic mail with 
<A HREF="../tips/finger.html">other users on your local system</A>.  Most systems also
allow you to exchange mail with users on 
<A HREF="../glossary/gr.html#remotehost">remote systems</A>.</P>

<P>Electronic mail is very quick. Messages will reach users
on the same system almost immediately; users on systems
elsewhere in this country, or other countries, in a few
minutes, or hours at most.</P>

